RACE.RACE_TEXT: BELTERRA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, For Each $2,500 To $10,000 1 lb. (Ohio Registered Foals Preferred)(Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $7,500). (If transferred to the Main Track, this race will be run at One Mile and 70 Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VOGELSANG between horses first turn chasing leader to the stretch, cleared. SWIGERT well rated while saving ground throughout, no match for winner. AMATTEROFPRINCIPLE off rail trip to far turn, ran on for the show spot in the lane. CASINO ANNIE bobbled a bit at the start, quick to the front, faltered far turn. ARTEMUS SWEETHEART broke very slowly with little chance throughout from that point. CANCERFREE KIDS tried to keep up on the backstretch with nothing left in the final furlong. BONITA D'ORO was through early and dropped far back. FELLA'S SISTER never factored throughout. Race was hand timed due to a bad sensor on the turf course, all turf races will be hand timed for the remainder of the meet. Acm
